Note:
RUNA BENCHMARK RUNNER - Performance Benchmark Suite Entry Point

This file handles Runa benchmark execution and performance testing.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Discover benchmark files matching naming conventions (bench_*.runa, *_bench.runa)
- Execute each benchmark multiple iterations for statistical accuracy
- Compute statistics (min, max, mean, median, standard deviation) for each benchmark
- Compare results against a stored baseline for regression detection
- Report results in a formatted table with statistical summaries

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Benchmark runner ensures Runa compiler and runtime performance is tracked over time
- Proper statistical computation ensures reliable performance measurements
- Baseline comparison enables automatic performance regression detection

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- BenchmarkResult type for per-benchmark statistical data
- discover_benchmarks to scan directories for benchmark files
- execute_benchmark to run a single benchmark N iterations and collect timings
- compute_statistics to calculate min/max/mean/median/stddev from raw timings
- compare_with_baseline to detect regressions against stored baseline results
- report_results to display formatted benchmark report
- run_benchmarks as the top-level entry point

Dependencies:
- Imports compiler/internal/string_utils.runa for string operations
- Imports compiler/internal/file_utils.runa for file read/write operations
- Imports compiler/internal/memory_utils.runa for memory allocation
- Imports compiler/internal/time_utils.runa for precise timing
- Imports compiler/internal/arena_utils.runa for arena-scoped allocation
:End Note

Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils
Import "compiler/internal/file_utils.runa" as FileUtils
Import "compiler/internal/memory_utils.runa" as MemoryUtils
Import "compiler/internal/time_utils.runa" as TimeUtils
Import "compiler/internal/arena_utils.runa" as ArenaUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Benchmark Runner Constants
Note: ============================================================================

Constant BENCH_TOOL_VERSION as Integer is 1
Constant BENCH_TOOL_SUCCESS as Integer is 0
Constant BENCH_TOOL_FAILURE as Integer is 1
Constant BENCH_TOOL_INVALID_ARGS as Integer is 2
Constant BENCH_TOOL_REGRESSION as Integer is 3

Constant BENCH_DEFAULT_ITERATIONS as Integer is 10
Constant BENCH_DEFAULT_WARMUP as Integer is 3
Constant BENCH_MAX_BENCHMARKS as Integer is 1024
Constant BENCH_REGRESSION_THRESHOLD_PCT as Integer is 10   Note: 10% regression threshold

Note: BenchmarkResult memory layout (80 bytes):
Note: offset  0: name (8 bytes) - Pointer to benchmark name string
Note: offset  8: iterations (8 bytes) - Number of iterations executed
Note: offset 16: min_ns (8 bytes) - Minimum time in nanoseconds
Note: offset 24: max_ns (8 bytes) - Maximum time in nanoseconds
Note: offset 32: mean_ns (8 bytes) - Mean time in nanoseconds
Note: offset 40: median_ns (8 bytes) - Median time in nanoseconds
Note: offset 48: stddev_ns (8 bytes) - Standard deviation in nanoseconds
Note: offset 56: total_ns (8 bytes) - Total time across all iterations
Note: offset 64: raw_timings (8 bytes) - Pointer to array of per-iteration timings (Integer[])
Note: offset 72: is_regression (8 bytes) - Boolean: 1 if this benchmark regressed vs baseline

Constant BENCH_RESULT_SIZE as Integer is 80

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Benchmark Discovery
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "discover_benchmarks" takes directory_path as Integer, arena as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Scan a directory for benchmark files matching naming conventions
    Note: Patterns: bench_*.runa and *_bench.runa
    Note: Returns pointer to ArrayList of file path strings, or 0 on failure

    If directory_path is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNABENCH ERROR] Cannot discover benchmarks: directory path is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    If arena is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNABENCH ERROR] Cannot discover benchmarks: arena is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let all_files be directory_list_files(directory_path, arena)
    If all_files is equal to 0:
        Let err_msg be string_concat("[RUNABENCH ERROR] Cannot list directory: ", directory_path)
        Alert err_msg
        deallocate(err_msg)
        Return 0
    End If

    Let bench_files be arraylist_create(BENCH_MAX_BENCHMARKS, 8, arena)
    If bench_files is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let file_count be arraylist_length(all_files)
    Let idx be 0

    While idx is less than file_count:
        Let entry_ptr be arraylist_get(all_files, idx)
        If entry_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let file_name be memory_get_pointer(entry_ptr, 0)
            If file_name is not equal to 0:
                Let is_bench be 0

                Note: Check for bench_ prefix with .runa suffix
                Let has_bench_prefix be string_starts_with(file_name, "bench_")
                If has_bench_prefix is equal to 1:
                    Let has_runa_suffix be string_ends_with(file_name, ".runa")
                    If has_runa_suffix is equal to 1:
                        Set is_bench to 1
                    End If
                End If

                Note: Check for _bench.runa suffix
                If is_bench is equal to 0:
                    Let has_bench_suffix be string_ends_with(file_name, "_bench.runa")
                    If has_bench_suffix is equal to 1:
                        Set is_bench to 1
                    End If
                End If

                If is_bench is equal to 1:
                    Let path_sep be string_concat(directory_path, "/")
                    Let full_path be string_concat(path_sep, file_name)
                    deallocate(path_sep)
                    Let path_copy be string_duplicate(full_path, arena)
                    deallocate(full_path)
                    arraylist_append(bench_files, path_copy)
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While

    Return bench_files
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Single Benchmark Execution
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "execute_benchmark" takes bench_path as Integer, iterations as Integer, warmup as Integer, arena as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Compile and run a benchmark file multiple times, collecting per-iteration timings
    Note: Performs warmup iterations first (not counted), then measured iterations
    Note: Returns pointer to BenchmarkResult, or 0 on failure

    If bench_path is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNABENCH ERROR] Cannot execute: benchmark path is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    If arena is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNABENCH ERROR] Cannot execute: arena is null"
        Return 0
    End If

    If iterations is less than 1:
        Set iterations to BENCH_DEFAULT_ITERATIONS
    End If

    If warmup is less than 0:
        Set warmup to BENCH_DEFAULT_WARMUP
    End If

    Note: Extract benchmark name from file path
    Let file_name be file_basename(bench_path, arena)
    If file_name is equal to 0:
        Set file_name to bench_path
    End If
    Let name_len be string_length(file_name)
    Let bench_name_len be name_len minus 5   Note: Remove ".runa"
    Let bench_name be file_name
    If bench_name_len is greater than 0:
        Set bench_name to string_substring(file_name, 0, bench_name_len, arena)
    End If

    Note: Compile the benchmark
    Let build_ctx be create_build_context(arena)
    If build_ctx is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNABENCH ERROR] Failed to create build context"
        Return 0
    End If

    add_source_file(build_ctx, bench_path)
    memory_set_integer(build_ctx, 16, 2)  Note: Optimize for speed (BUILD_OPT_SPEED)

    Let compile_result be build_all(build_ctx)
    If compile_result is not equal to 0:
        Let err_msg be string_concat("[RUNABENCH ERROR] Compilation failed: ", bench_path)
        Alert err_msg
        deallocate(err_msg)
        Return 0
    End If

    Let exe_path be memory_get_pointer(build_ctx, 144)
    If exe_path is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNABENCH ERROR] No executable produced"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate result structure
    Let result be arena_allocate(arena, BENCH_RESULT_SIZE, 8)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    memory_zero(result, BENCH_RESULT_SIZE)

    memory_set_pointer(result, 0, bench_name)
    memory_set_integer(result, 8, iterations)

    Note: Allocate raw timings array
    Let timings_size be iterations multiplied by 8
    Let timings be arena_allocate(arena, timings_size, 8)
    If timings is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    memory_zero(timings, timings_size)
    memory_set_pointer(result, 64, timings)

    Note: Warmup phase (results discarded)
    Let warmup_idx be 0
    While warmup_idx is less than warmup:
        Let warmup_result be execute_process(exe_path)
        Set warmup_idx to warmup_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note: Measured iterations
    Let total_ns be 0
    Let min_ns be 999999999999
    Let max_ns be 0

    Let iter_idx be 0
    While iter_idx is less than iterations:
        Note: Time each iteration using monotonic clock
        Let start_time be time_now_monotonic(arena)

        Let exec_result be execute_process(exe_path)

        Let end_time be time_now_monotonic(arena)
        Let elapsed_ns be time_diff_ns(start_time, end_time)

        Note: Store this timing
        Let timing_offset be iter_idx multiplied by 8
        memory_set_integer(timings, timing_offset, elapsed_ns)

        Note: Update running statistics
        Set total_ns to total_ns plus elapsed_ns

        If elapsed_ns is less than min_ns:
            Set min_ns to elapsed_ns
        End If

        If elapsed_ns is greater than max_ns:
            Set max_ns to elapsed_ns
        End If

        Set iter_idx to iter_idx plus 1
    End While

    memory_set_integer(result, 16, min_ns)
    memory_set_integer(result, 24, max_ns)
    memory_set_integer(result, 56, total_ns)

    Note: Compute full statistics
    Let stats_result be compute_statistics(result)

    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Statistical Computation
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "compute_statistics" takes result as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Compute mean, median, and standard deviation from raw timings
    Note: Operates in-place on the BenchmarkResult structure
    Note: Returns 0 on success

    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let iterations be memory_get_integer(result, 8)
    Let total_ns be memory_get_integer(result, 56)
    Let timings be memory_get_pointer(result, 64)

    If iterations is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    If timings is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Compute mean
    Let mean_ns be total_ns divided by iterations
    memory_set_integer(result, 32, mean_ns)

    Note: Compute median: sort the timings array, then take the middle element
    Note: Copy timings for sorting (preserve original order)
    Let sorted_size be iterations multiplied by 8
    Let sorted be allocate(sorted_size)
    If sorted is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    memory_copy(sorted, timings, sorted_size)

    Note: Insertion sort on the sorted array
    Let sort_i be 1
    While sort_i is less than iterations:
        Let sort_i_offset be sort_i multiplied by 8
        Let key be memory_get_integer(sorted, sort_i_offset)
        Let sort_j be sort_i minus 1

        Let continue_sort be 1
        While continue_sort is equal to 1:
            If sort_j is less than 0:
                Set continue_sort to 0
            Otherwise:
                Let sort_j_offset be sort_j multiplied by 8
                Let sort_j_val be memory_get_integer(sorted, sort_j_offset)
                If sort_j_val is greater than key:
                    Note: Shift element right
                    Let next_j_offset be sort_j_offset plus 8
                    memory_set_integer(sorted, next_j_offset, sort_j_val)
                    Set sort_j to sort_j minus 1
                Otherwise:
                    Set continue_sort to 0
                End If
            End If
        End While

        Let insert_offset be sort_j plus 1
        Let insert_byte_offset be insert_offset multiplied by 8
        memory_set_integer(sorted, insert_byte_offset, key)

        Set sort_i to sort_i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Get median (middle element for odd count, average of two middle for even)
    Let mid be iterations divided by 2
    Let is_even be iterations minus mid multiplied by 2
    Note: If iterations == mid * 2, it's even
    Let mid_offset be mid multiplied by 8
    Let median_ns be memory_get_integer(sorted, mid_offset)

    Let check_even be mid multiplied by 2
    If check_even is equal to iterations:
        Note: Even number of elements: average the two middle values
        Let mid_minus_1_offset be mid minus 1
        Let mid_m1_byte_offset be mid_minus_1_offset multiplied by 8
        Let lower_mid be memory_get_integer(sorted, mid_m1_byte_offset)
        Set median_ns to lower_mid plus median_ns
        Set median_ns to median_ns divided by 2
    End If

    memory_set_integer(result, 40, median_ns)

    Note: Compute standard deviation
    Note: stddev = sqrt(sum((x_i - mean)^2) / N)
    Note: Using integer approximation: we compute variance then approximate sqrt
    Let variance_sum be 0
    Let var_idx be 0
    While var_idx is less than iterations:
        Let var_offset be var_idx multiplied by 8
        Let timing_val be memory_get_integer(sorted, var_offset)
        Let diff be timing_val minus mean_ns
        Let diff_squared be diff multiplied by diff
        Set variance_sum to variance_sum plus diff_squared
        Set var_idx to var_idx plus 1
    End While

    Let variance be variance_sum divided by iterations

    Note: Integer square root approximation using Newton's method
    Let stddev be integer_sqrt(variance)
    memory_set_integer(result, 48, stddev)

    deallocate(sorted)
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "integer_sqrt" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Compute integer square root using Newton's method (Babylonian method)
    Note: Returns floor(sqrt(value))

    If value is less than 2:
        Return value
    End If

    Let guess be value divided by 2
    Let prev_guess be 0

    Let iterations be 0
    Let max_iterations be 64

    While iterations is less than max_iterations:
        Let new_guess be guess plus value divided by guess
        Set new_guess to new_guess divided by 2

        Note: Check for convergence
        Let diff be new_guess minus guess
        If diff is equal to 0:
            Set iterations to max_iterations    Note: Converged, exit
        Otherwise:
            If diff is equal to 1:
                Set iterations to max_iterations    Note: Close enough
            Otherwise:
                If diff is equal to -1:
                    Set iterations to max_iterations
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set prev_guess to guess
        Set guess to new_guess
        Set iterations to iterations plus 1
    End While

    Note: Verify: if guess*guess > value, use guess-1
    Let check be guess multiplied by guess
    If check is greater than value:
        Set guess to guess minus 1
    End If

    Return guess
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Baseline Comparison
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "compare_with_baseline" takes results as Integer, baseline_path as Integer, arena as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Compare current benchmark results against a stored baseline file
    Note: The baseline file format is: name mean_ns (one per line)
    Note: Returns number of regressions detected

    If results is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If baseline_path is equal to 0:
        Display "[RUNABENCH] No baseline file specified, skipping comparison"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let baseline_content be runtime_read_file(baseline_path)
    If baseline_content is equal to 0:
        Display "[RUNABENCH] No baseline file found, skipping comparison"
        Return 0
    End If

    Display "[RUNABENCH] Comparing against baseline: "
    Display baseline_path

    Let regressions be 0
    Let result_count be arraylist_length(results)
    Let content_len be string_length(baseline_content)

    Note: Parse baseline file line by line
    Let base_pos be 0
    While base_pos is less than content_len:
        Let line_start be base_pos
        Let line_end be string_index_of_from(baseline_content, 10, base_pos)
        If line_end is less than 0:
            Set line_end to content_len
        End If

        Let line_len be line_end minus line_start
        Let line be string_substring(baseline_content, line_start, line_len, arena)

        If line is not equal to 0:
            Let trimmed be string_trim(line, arena)
            If trimmed is not equal to 0:
                Let trimmed_len be string_length(trimmed)
                If trimmed_len is greater than 0:
                    Note: Parse "name mean_ns" format
                    Let space_pos be string_index_of(trimmed, 32)
                    If space_pos is greater than 0:
                        Let base_name be string_substring(trimmed, 0, space_pos, arena)
                        Let base_time_str be string_substring_from(trimmed, space_pos plus 1, arena)
                        Let base_time_trimmed be string_trim(base_time_str, arena)
                        Let base_mean_ns be string_to_integer(base_time_trimmed)

                        Note: Find matching result
                        Let res_idx be 0
                        While res_idx is less than result_count:
                            Let res_ptr be arraylist_get(results, res_idx)
                            If res_ptr is not equal to 0:
                                Let res be memory_get_pointer(res_ptr, 0)
                                If res is not equal to 0:
                                    Let res_name be memory_get_pointer(res, 0)
                                    If res_name is not equal to 0:
                                        Let names_match be string_equals(res_name, base_name)
                                        If names_match is equal to 1:
                                            Let current_mean be memory_get_integer(res, 32)

                                            Note: Check for regression: current > baseline * (1 + threshold/100)
                                            Let threshold_factor be base_mean_ns multiplied by BENCH_REGRESSION_THRESHOLD_PCT
                                            Let threshold_ns be threshold_factor divided by 100
                                            Let regression_limit be base_mean_ns plus threshold_ns

                                            If current_mean is greater than regression_limit:
                                                memory_set_integer(res, 72, 1)
                                                Set regressions to regressions plus 1

                                                Let pct_change be current_mean minus base_mean_ns
                                                Let pct_change_scaled be pct_change multiplied by 100
                                                Let pct_actual be pct_change_scaled divided by base_mean_ns

                                                Let reg_msg be string_concat("[RUNABENCH REGRESSION] ", res_name)
                                                Let reg_msg2 be string_concat(reg_msg, " regressed by ")
                                                deallocate(reg_msg)
                                                Let pct_str be integer_to_string(pct_actual, arena)
                                                Let reg_msg3 be string_concat(reg_msg2, pct_str)
                                                deallocate(reg_msg2)
                                                Let reg_msg4 be string_concat(reg_msg3, "%")
                                                deallocate(reg_msg3)
                                                Alert reg_msg4
                                                deallocate(reg_msg4)
                                            End If

                                            Set res_idx to result_count   Note: Found match, stop searching
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                            Set res_idx to res_idx plus 1
                        End While
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set base_pos to line_end plus 1
    End While

    deallocate(baseline_content)

    If regressions is equal to 0:
        Display "[RUNABENCH] No regressions detected"
    Otherwise:
        Alert "[RUNABENCH] "
        Display regressions
        Alert " regression(s) detected!"
    End If

    Return regressions
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Results Reporting
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "report_results" takes results as Integer, arena as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Display formatted benchmark results table
    Note: Returns 0 on success

    If results is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNABENCH ERROR] Cannot report: results is null"
        Return 1
    End If

    Let result_count be arraylist_length(results)

    Display "=================================================================="
    Display "[RUNABENCH] Benchmark Results"
    Display "=================================================================="
    Display "  Name                  Iters   Min(ms)  Mean(ms)  Med(ms)  StdDev(ms)"
    Display "------------------------------------------------------------------"

    Let idx be 0
    While idx is less than result_count:
        Let res_ptr be arraylist_get(results, idx)
        If res_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let res be memory_get_pointer(res_ptr, 0)
            If res is not equal to 0:
                Let name be memory_get_pointer(res, 0)
                Let iterations be memory_get_integer(res, 8)
                Let min_ns be memory_get_integer(res, 16)
                Let mean_ns be memory_get_integer(res, 32)
                Let median_ns be memory_get_integer(res, 40)
                Let stddev_ns be memory_get_integer(res, 48)
                Let is_regression be memory_get_integer(res, 72)

                Note: Convert nanoseconds to milliseconds for display
                Let min_ms be min_ns divided by 1000000
                Let mean_ms be mean_ns divided by 1000000
                Let median_ms be median_ns divided by 1000000
                Let stddev_ms be stddev_ns divided by 1000000

                If is_regression is equal to 1:
                    Display "! "
                Otherwise:
                    Display "  "
                End If

                If name is not equal to 0:
                    Display name
                End If
                Display "  "
                Display iterations
                Display "  "
                Display min_ms
                Display "  "
                Display mean_ms
                Display "  "
                Display median_ms
                Display "  "
                Display stddev_ms

                If is_regression is equal to 1:
                    Display "  [REGRESSION]"
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While

    Display "=================================================================="

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Top-Level Entry Point
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "run_benchmarks" takes argc as Integer, argv as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Main entry point for the benchmark runner
    Note: Discovers benchmarks, executes them, computes statistics, reports results
    Note: Returns exit code (0 = success, 3 = regression detected)

    If argc is less than 2:
        Alert "[RUNABENCH] Usage: runa bench <directory> [options]"
        Alert "[RUNABENCH] Options:"
        Alert "[RUNABENCH]   --iterations N    Number of measured iterations (default: 10)"
        Alert "[RUNABENCH]   --warmup N        Number of warmup iterations (default: 3)"
        Alert "[RUNABENCH]   --baseline <file> Compare against baseline results"
        Alert "[RUNABENCH]   --save <file>     Save results as new baseline"
        Alert "[RUNABENCH]   --verbose         Enable verbose output"
        Return BENCH_TOOL_INVALID_ARGS
    End If

    Let arena be arena_create(262144)
    If arena is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNABENCH ERROR] Failed to create arena"
        Return BENCH_TOOL_FAILURE
    End If

    Let bench_dir be 0
    Let iterations be BENCH_DEFAULT_ITERATIONS
    Let warmup be BENCH_DEFAULT_WARMUP
    Let baseline_path be 0
    Let save_path be 0
    Let is_verbose be 0
    Let ptr_size be 8
    Let i be 1

    While i is less than argc:
        Let arg_offset be i multiplied by ptr_size
        Let arg_ptr be argv plus arg_offset
        Let arg be memory_get_pointer(arg_ptr, 0)

        If arg is not equal to 0:
            Let is_iter be string_equals(arg, "--iterations")
            If is_iter is equal to 1:
                Set i to i plus 1
                If i is less than argc:
                    Let next_offset be i multiplied by ptr_size
                    Let next_ptr be argv plus next_offset
                    Let iter_str be memory_get_pointer(next_ptr, 0)
                    If iter_str is not equal to 0:
                        Set iterations to string_to_integer(iter_str)
                        If iterations is less than 1:
                            Set iterations to BENCH_DEFAULT_ITERATIONS
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            Otherwise:
                Let is_warmup be string_equals(arg, "--warmup")
                If is_warmup is equal to 1:
                    Set i to i plus 1
                    If i is less than argc:
                        Let next_offset be i multiplied by ptr_size
                        Let next_ptr be argv plus next_offset
                        Let warmup_str be memory_get_pointer(next_ptr, 0)
                        If warmup_str is not equal to 0:
                            Set warmup to string_to_integer(warmup_str)
                        End If
                    End If
                Otherwise:
                    Let is_baseline be string_equals(arg, "--baseline")
                    If is_baseline is equal to 1:
                        Set i to i plus 1
                        If i is less than argc:
                            Let next_offset be i multiplied by ptr_size
                            Let next_ptr be argv plus next_offset
                            Set baseline_path to memory_get_pointer(next_ptr, 0)
                        End If
                    Otherwise:
                        Let is_save be string_equals(arg, "--save")
                        If is_save is equal to 1:
                            Set i to i plus 1
                            If i is less than argc:
                                Let next_offset be i multiplied by ptr_size
                                Let next_ptr be argv plus next_offset
                                Set save_path to memory_get_pointer(next_ptr, 0)
                            End If
                        Otherwise:
                            Let is_verbose_flag be string_equals(arg, "--verbose")
                            If is_verbose_flag is equal to 1:
                                Set is_verbose to 1
                            Otherwise:
                                Set bench_dir to arg
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    If bench_dir is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNABENCH ERROR] No benchmark directory specified"
        arena_destroy(arena)
        Return BENCH_TOOL_INVALID_ARGS
    End If

    Note: Discover benchmarks
    Let bench_files be discover_benchmarks(bench_dir, arena)
    If bench_files is equal to 0:
        Alert "[RUNABENCH] No benchmark files found"
        arena_destroy(arena)
        Return BENCH_TOOL_SUCCESS
    End If

    Let file_count be arraylist_length(bench_files)
    If file_count is equal to 0:
        Display "[RUNABENCH] No benchmark files found in: "
        Display bench_dir
        arena_destroy(arena)
        Return BENCH_TOOL_SUCCESS
    End If

    Display "[RUNABENCH] Discovered "
    Display file_count
    Display " benchmark(s)"
    Display "[RUNABENCH] Iterations: "
    Display iterations
    Display ", Warmup: "
    Display warmup

    Note: Execute each benchmark
    Let all_results be arraylist_create(file_count, 8, arena)
    If all_results is equal to 0:
        arena_destroy(arena)
        Return BENCH_TOOL_FAILURE
    End If

    Let exec_idx be 0
    While exec_idx is less than file_count:
        Let file_ptr be arraylist_get(bench_files, exec_idx)
        If file_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let bench_path be memory_get_pointer(file_ptr, 0)
            If bench_path is not equal to 0:
                If is_verbose is equal to 1:
                    Let run_msg be string_concat("[RUNABENCH] Running: ", bench_path)
                    Display run_msg
                    deallocate(run_msg)
                End If

                Let result be execute_benchmark(bench_path, iterations, warmup, arena)
                If result is not equal to 0:
                    arraylist_append(all_results, result)
                Otherwise:
                    Let err_msg be string_concat("[RUNABENCH WARNING] Failed to run: ", bench_path)
                    Alert err_msg
                    deallocate(err_msg)
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set exec_idx to exec_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note: Compare with baseline if provided
    Let regressions be 0
    If baseline_path is not equal to 0:
        Set regressions to compare_with_baseline(all_results, baseline_path, arena)
    End If

    Note: Report results
    Let report_status be report_results(all_results, arena)

    Note: Save results as baseline if requested
    If save_path is not equal to 0:
        Let save_content be string_duplicate("", arena)
        Let save_count be arraylist_length(all_results)
        Let save_idx be 0
        While save_idx is less than save_count:
            Let res_ptr be arraylist_get(all_results, save_idx)
            If res_ptr is not equal to 0:
                Let res be memory_get_pointer(res_ptr, 0)
                If res is not equal to 0:
                    Let name be memory_get_pointer(res, 0)
                    Let mean_ns be memory_get_integer(res, 32)
                    If name is not equal to 0:
                        Let line_part be string_concat(name, " ")
                        Let mean_str be integer_to_string(mean_ns, arena)
                        Let line_part2 be string_concat(line_part, mean_str)
                        deallocate(line_part)
                        Let line_with_nl be string_concat(line_part2, "\n")
                        deallocate(line_part2)
                        Let new_content be string_concat(save_content, line_with_nl)
                        deallocate(line_with_nl)
                        Set save_content to string_duplicate(new_content, arena)
                        deallocate(new_content)
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            Set save_idx to save_idx plus 1
        End While

        Let save_len be string_length(save_content)
        Let write_result be runtime_write_file(save_path, save_content, save_len)
        If write_result is equal to 0:
            Display "[RUNABENCH] Baseline saved to: "
            Display save_path
        Otherwise:
            Alert "[RUNABENCH WARNING] Failed to save baseline"
        End If
    End If

    arena_destroy(arena)

    If regressions is greater than 0:
        Return BENCH_TOOL_REGRESSION
    End If

    Return BENCH_TOOL_SUCCESS
End Process
